# Pixel Perfect — Design Negativregeln

**Firma:** HorosCode · **Produkt:** HorosCloud

> **The mockup is the truth.** Fidelity target: **98 / 100**.

## Never Do This

- **Never** "improve" the layout — rearrange, remove, or add elements not in the mockup
- **Never** modernize visuals — rounded corners, shadows, gradients the mockup lacks
- **Never** simplify — merge buttons, collapse sections, hide "clutter"
- **Never** substitute colors, fonts, or spacing with "close enough" values
- **Never** use personal taste as justification for any visual change
- **Never** skip a visible mockup element because it seems redundant

## Always Do This

- Match **exact** spacing (±1 px tolerance at review)
- Match **exact** typography: family, size, weight, line-height
- Match **exact** colors via tokens from `docs/design-memory.md`
- Match **exact** border-radius, borders, shadows when present in mockup
- Copy **exact** label text from mockup in Pass 1

## Token Rule

Do not invent hex values inline in AXAML:

```xml
<!-- WRONG -->
<Border Background="#1E293B" Padding="18" />

<!-- RIGHT -->
<Border Background="{DynamicResource BrushSurfaceDefault}"
        Padding="{DynamicResource Spacing4}" />
```

New mockup values → add to `docs/design-memory.md` first, then `DesignTokens.axaml`.

## Allowed Deviation

Only with **explicit user approval** in chat — document what changed and why.

